Description:
Massive price reduction, owner must sell!
Feel part of Collingwoods brewing history, as you make a grand entrance through the original faade of the James Hood and Co Malt House, and the large copper door, into the Silos development. Park your bike in the bike racks, and visit the gym, before heading up to the top floor of the warehouse apartments, where you will find this 2 bedroom apartment. Step directly into the open plan kitchen and living area with, island bench, timber floors, stone bench tops, ducted heating and cooling, and then directly onto the generous balcony, perfect, for relaxed weekend breakfasts. Not limited for storage the master bedroom includes a whole wall, of mirrored built in robes, and a little nook perfect for a desk or extra storage. A Euro laundry, with extra storage, and a stylish generous bathroom complete the apartments smart use of space, and design, however if you need it, a storage cage is located in the secure basement car park. A large covered decked area, with BBQ facilities and herb garden are there for the lucky residents in this small development, which fosters a community feel.
Islington Silos is conveniently located within a short walk to Smith Street, Brunswick Street and Melbourne CBD, giving you the amazing opportunity to wander down to your favourite, cafes, restaurants and iconic fashion stores. A stone's throw away from buses, trains and the Eastern Freeway this apartment is perfect for the owner occupier, or as a rental investment.
Insights: 208/55 Islington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Victorian warmth, contemporary flair
Two classic architectural styles fuse seamlessly in this elegant high-ceilinged residence, superbly positioned close to transport and just a short stroll to the cafe and shopping precincts of Brunswick Street and edgy Johnston Street. With abundant natural light and outdoor living space, this cleverly zoned home offers a versatile floor plan comprising 4 double bedrooms (two with expansive views), 2 designer bathrooms (main with walk-in shower and bath), custom kitchen (Belling induction cooktop, triple oven and pantry) open to spacious living/dining room, plus laundry. Including a secluded courtyard, al fresco entertaining area, workshop and off-street parking, this striking city-edge residence features large loft storage, polished hardwood floors, ample storage, period detail, split-system air conditioning and cabling.
Insights: 15 Forest Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 3 other 4 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Immediate Return on Investment
Exceptionally well-maintained one bedroom apartment with a possible return of 5.3% presents the perfect opportunity for investors to acquire their share of Collingwood's vibrant, city edge culture.
Featuring a modern and well-appointed kitchen with vast storage, a spacious and bright open plan living/dining area, stylish bedroom including large built-in robes and an immaculate central bathroom. Additional features include reverse cycle heating/cooling system in both the bedroom and living, secure car space on title, common courtyard, and secure intercom entry.

Oxford & Peel - Luxury, Lifestyle, Location
Apartment 310 - A stylish and sustainable development by award-winning Jackson Clements Burrows Architects sets the scene for this third-floor apartment guaranteed to please with its spacious design, deluxe features and fabulous city views. Elegant and efficient, the apartment's vogue interior boasts 2 double bedrooms (both with custom-fitted robes and study desks), deluxe master ensuite and main central bathroom, sleek kitchen with stainless steel benchtops and splashbacks, integrated dishwasher and Miele cooking appliances, plus light-filled open living/meals area leading out to a private terrace with elevated city views and signature louvres for privacy. Privately tucked away off to the side of the acclaimed 'Islington Silos' with its fabulous communal entertainment area and fitted gym; this high-quality 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom home makes a stunning statement in secure, easy indoor-outdoor living including covered entertainment terrace, ducted heating/cooling, wide Oak floorboards, storage cage and basement car space on title. Stroll to Gertrude/Victoria Streets, Fitzroy Gardens, the Yarra and the city from this striking apartment comprising open-plan living/dining and excellent stone kitchen, main bedroom with ensuite, BIRs, laundry, abundance of natural light and intercom entry.

Description:
A landmark site across the ages
This refined city edge residence demonstrates the spectacular evolution of the former Yorkshire Brewery site from an iconic industrial landmark to a residential address of exceptional contemporary luxury. The passage of progress ensures these evocative surroundings now provide a fabulous setting for inner city living in a location that since the 1860s has been a focal point in Collingwood, acknowledged as Melbourne's foundation suburb. Entered from Brewery Lane, this designer townhouse features inviting downstairs living and dining areas that open to an elegant ground level terrace and are complemented by the form and function of a kitchen zone where marble surfaces and Miele appliances reflect an impressive commitment to quality. Upstairs, a main bedroom with an ensuite and a balcony retreat is accompanied by two further bedrooms, a superb central bathroom and a dedicated study space. Secure car parking adds to the attraction, around the corner from Gertrude Street cafes and trams.
Insights: 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
The space to create your Sackville Street sanctuary
A rare double-fronted delight freestanding on a surprisingly large inner-city block (269m2 approx), this comfortable 1920s residence of unique size and scope opens to a spacious north-facing rear garden. Enjoyed by the one owner for over 20 years, this very comfortable period home includes the bonus of a side driveway and has exciting potential to further renovate or extend (STCA) if required. Take full advantage of this classic home's superb dimensions that currently include 2 sizable bedrooms, free-flowing living room, bright dining room, updated kitchen with stainless-steel appliances, bathroom, laundry, gas heating, alarm system, period charm and leafy north-facing backyard with vegetable garden.

An impressive inner-urban sanctuary just a heartbeat to all the excitement of Smith and Brunswick Streets, this sensational modern townhouse is staged over 3 levels rising to a spectacular terrace with city views. Description:
Industrial chic, irresistible locale
Merging a sense of history with an uber-cool latte lifestyle, this sensational multi-level apartment offers a dynamic inner-city experience in the iconic Foy and Gibson precinct. There's a New York vibe happening here, both inside and out, with a heady mix of galleries, boutiques, bars, cafes and restaurants all within metres of your door and more than a touch of industrial-chic throughout a Manhattan style interior. Secure and intriguing, accessed via stunning open air entrance, the 2 bedroom/2 bathroom design features Oregon-beams, recycled timber floors and plenty of natural light through quality kitchen/living areas and mezzanine-style study. French doors from the lower bedroom open to the communal bluestone terrace whilst the upper bedroom takes in the night-sky. Electric heating, Euro laundry, intercom entry and secure parking deliver a carefree lifestyle or brilliant investment package in last 12 months returning $65,000 on Airbnb.
Insights: 4/76 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
BREATHTAKING CITY VIEWS
Positioned within 5 minutes' walk of North Richmond Station and Victoria Parade trams, this former grain storehouse provides a fresh and modern aesthetic, whilst retaining an industrial warehouse feel.
The "Islington Silos" have made a defining contribution to the transformation of the once industrial hub into arguably the most sought after and trendiest suburbs in Melbourne.
Entering the apartment from the elevator, the generous entry foyer leads to an expansive open living and dining area before attention is drawn to the sophisticated and well-appointed kitchen featuring vast storage, generous bench space and top line appliances. The private balcony offers stunning views of the Melbourne CBD, with plenty of room to unwind and enjoy the company of friends.
The property includes three bedrooms; the master with walk-in robe and a fully tiled en-suite and two remaining bedrooms with built-in robes and plenty of natural light, and exceptional views.
Additional features include ducted heating and cooling throughout, video intercom entry, secure undercover car space with a substantial lock up storage cage, an entertaining area including BBQ and use of a well-equipped gym.
This property offers the very best of contemporary living; an abundance of space, light, architectural flair and urban chic and is immediately accessible to the all that Collingwood has to offer
Insights: 701/55 Islington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 18 other 3 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.
